Example structure in `/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/lol/src/components/`:
- `action_panel/` - ActionPanel, ActionsDropdown with separate SCSS files
- `form/` - Form wrapper, FormTextField, FormCheckbox, FormDropdown, FormDatePicker, FormTextArea, FormField
- `list/` - List, ListItem, ListSection with list_context
- `grid/` - Grid, GridItem with grid_context
- `toast/` - Toast, ToastContainer with separate container SCSS
- `detail/` - Detail, DetailMetadata with nested metadata sub-components

### Typical Component Pattern
Components are minimal, composable React functions:
- Props are typed with interfaces (no PropTypes)
- SCSS file imported at top of component
- Children and state managed through props and React hooks
- Context used for shared state within component trees (List, Grid)

